# 💡 Founder Recommendation

As a solo founder, you don't need a huge QA team.

Use a simple three-stage testing strategy:

### Stage 1 – Self Testing

Test every new feature yourself.

↓

### Stage 2 – Family & Friends

Ask 5–10 people with different phones and different blood reports to try the app.

↓

### Stage 3 – Small Beta

Invite 20–50 real users. Watch where they struggle, collect feedback, and improve before a wider launch.

This approach gives you meaningful feedback without requiring a large testing budget.

